# General rules for Cursor
- Always use Vue 3 + Vite.
- Use shadcn/ui as the base for UI components.
- Styling through TailwindCSS.
- Avoid libraries like Bootstrap, MaterialUI.
- Write code comments in English.
 
## Running the notary-vue project

Requirements: Node 20 (LTS) and npm.

1. Navigate to the project directory:

```bash
cd notary-vue
```

2. Install dependencies:

```bash
npm install
```

3. Run development server:

```bash
npm run dev
```

Default port: 5173.

# UI Conventions – Tailwind + shadcn-vue

This document describes the rules for using Tailwind and shadcn-vue components in our project.

⸻

1. Directory structure
	•	src/components/ui/* – components generated by shadcn-vue CLI (atoms, molecules).
	•	src/components/* – domain components (e.g. InvoiceList.vue) using ui/*.
	•	src/lib/* – utilities, helper functions, logic without UI.

⸻

2. Component naming
	•	shadcn components have Ui prefix, e.g. UiButton, UiCard.
	•	Domain components – PascalCase, e.g. InvoiceList.
	•	Always default export from .vue.

⸻

3. Tailwind – class usage
	•	Class order: enforced by prettier-plugin-tailwindcss.
	•	Prefer gap-* instead of margins for spacing.
	•	Arbitrary values (w-[37px]) only exceptionally, mark TODO.
	•	If a class set repeats 3+ times → extract component or use @apply.

⸻

4. Variants and sizes
	•	Managed by class-variance-authority or tailwind-variants.
	•	Standard values:
	•	variant: default | destructive | outline | ghost | link
	•	size: sm | md | lg | icon
	•	Defaults: variant="default", size="md".

⸻

5. Tokens and colors
	•	Brand colors in tailwind.config.cjs → theme.extend.colors.
	•	We use CSS variables (--primary, --secondary, --muted, --accent, --destructive).
	•	We don't use hex values in code.

⸻

6. Responsiveness
	•	Mobile-first, then md, lg.
	•	Max 2 breakpoints per component.

⸻

7. Limits and simplicity
	•	Max 10 classes per element.
	•	Max 3 nesting levels for containers.

⸻

8. Accessibility
	•	Interactive elements must have focus-visible:*.
	•	disabled: opacity-*, cursor-not-allowed, aria-disabled="true".
	•	We ensure contrast and hit-area size.

⸻

9. Code review checklist
	•	No arbitrary values without justification.
	•	Classes sorted (Prettier plugin).
	•	Repeated patterns → component or @apply.
	•	Focus-states and aria-attributes correct.
	•	Component ≤10 classes / ≤3 containers.

⸻

10. How to add shadcn-vue components

npx shadcn-vue@latest add button

File goes to src/components/ui/. Import as UiButton.

⸻

11. Example

Wrong:

<div class="w-full p-4 bg-white rounded-lg shadow flex items-center justify-between mt-4 mb-8 sm:flex-col hover:bg-gray-50 text-gray-800"></div>

Good:

<UiCard class="mt-4 mb-8">
  <div class="flex items-center justify-between sm:flex-col">
    <p class="text-gray-800">Hello World</p>
  </div>
</UiCard>